Objectify, java.lang.Cloneable
public class ObjectifyImplTxn
extends ObjectifyImpl

Implementation for when we start a transaction. Maintains a separate session, but then copies all data into the original session on successful commit.

getTxn

public com.google.appengine.api.datastore.Transaction getTxn()
Description copied from interface: Objectify

Get the underlying transaction object associated with this Objectify instance. You typically do not need to use this; use transact() instead.

Note that this is *not* the same as DatastoreService.getCurrentTransaction(), which uses implicit transaction management. Objectify does not use implicit (thread local) transactions.

Specified by:
getTxn in interface Objectify
Overrides:
getTxn in class ObjectifyImpl
Returns:
the transaction associated with this Objectify instance, or null if no transaction is associated with this instance.

getTxnRaw

public com.google.appengine.api.datastore.Transaction getTxnRaw()
Description copied from class: ObjectifyImpl
Get the raw version, unwrapped by a proxy. The engine needs this to pass through to the AsyncDatastoreService, which might have given us a wrapped Transaction itself (ie, CachingAsyncDatastoreService).
